<subSubSection id="D3737A87FCAE0788D8BD7EEC6B6BF7FF" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="954498FA1817070648BC526532269CD4" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8975C58C49BAF0B377259A9964FDB5D6" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
The name is from the Latin word 
<taxonomicName id="B5406BBF3BCE894C51048DE4208DC755" authorityName="Liu" authorityYear="2022" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Synagelides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Synagelides triangulatus" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangulatus">
<emphasis id="55A2FEB1772456BC3C0FB119D74E4AA1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Synagelides triangulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, referring to the shape of the median septum; adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0C9AD6E88FA1389CA0D96A0ECBE091A6" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="00CF21FC2FF74126A3B6E5B4B2C3A4F0" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B65C4B64C36B621FF4DCD56338651A17" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
The female of this species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="63AF95308EE613735197F9821A02097B" authorityName="Logunov &amp; Hereward" authorityYear="2006" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Synagelides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Synagelides kosi" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kosi">
<emphasis id="16A809E2E99A87FF4CDAB4543F52BF10" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Synagelides kosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Logunov &amp; Hereward, 2006 (
<bibRefCitation id="EA0B7E373D9727EB89167D6747A48E48" author="Logunov, DV" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin-British Arachnological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" pagination="281 - 292" refId="B6" refString="Logunov, DV, Hereward, J, 2006. New species and synonymies in the genus Synagelides Strand in Boesenberg &amp; Strand, 1906 (Araneae: Salticidae). Bulletin-British Arachnological Society 13: 281 - 292" title="New species and synonymies in the genus Synagelides Strand in Boesenberg &amp; Strand, 1906 (Araneae: Salticidae)." volume="13" year="2006">Logunov and Hereward 2006</bibRefCitation>
: 285, figs 24, 32) and 
<taxonomicName id="A98F8DBE2A98CC953438AA788B3E7E7B" genus="S." lsidName="S. jinggangshanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="jinggangshanensis">
<emphasis id="A9137DD8B6C327B28CAD4E91074AC21E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. jinggangshanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="E5365E07B0B3ED903DF3ACAAECAE2A28" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4350.2.5" author="Liu, KK" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" pagination="291 - 300" refId="B5" refString="Liu, KK, Chen, ZW, Xu, X, Peng, XJ, 2017. Three new species of Synagelides Strand, 1906 from China (Araneae: Salticidae). Zootaxa 4350 (2): 291 - 300, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4350.2.5" title="Three new species of Synagelides Strand, 1906 from China (Araneae: Salticidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4350.2.5" volume="4350" year="2017">Liu et al., 2017</bibRefCitation>
(
<bibRefCitation id="0EA2545D0D686592C577D7AB0DDFD6CE" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4350.2.5" author="Liu, KK" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" pagination="291 - 300" refId="B5" refString="Liu, KK, Chen, ZW, Xu, X, Peng, XJ, 2017. Three new species of Synagelides Strand, 1906 from China (Araneae: Salticidae). Zootaxa 4350 (2): 291 - 300, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4350.2.5" title="Three new species of Synagelides Strand, 1906 from China (Araneae: Salticidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4350.2.5" volume="4350" year="2017">Liu et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
: 292, figs 1C, D, 2A, B; holotype examined) in having the C-shaped median part and the sloping, slender, tub-shaped posterior part of copulatory duct, but can be separated from them by (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3C0255A4013D66BB6D7C9E391B07916D" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Synagelides triangulatus sp. nov., holotype female A habitus, dorsal view B same, ventral view C epigyne, ventral view D same, dorsal view. Abbreviations: AR - atrial rim, At - atrium, CD - copulatory duct, CO - copulatory opening, EH - epigynal hood, FD - fertilization duct, GA - glandular appendages, MS - median septum, Spe - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A, B); 0.05 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.76800.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686172" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">12C, D</figureCitation>
) the broad, bell-shaped epigynal hood (vs relatively thin in 
<taxonomicName id="C58498F4182472979B0B19E3DB688273" genus="S." lsidName="S. kosi" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="kosi">
<emphasis id="2B24FF52D8AD1F90CD13F4D8701A7569" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. kosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6C1EB616F1C6A01BF4BE5E4AFEE5CABA" genus="S." lsidName="S. jinggangshanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="jinggangshanensis">
<emphasis id="79544BE537E4D064E1CD586FD1DAA8BC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. jinggangshanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the relatively broad triangular median septum (vs nearly T-shaped in 
<taxonomicName id="A490F0538FCCEAC53D5314363BAFA73C" genus="S." lsidName="S. kosi" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="kosi">
<emphasis id="B63D4F4D6BAD321BA98168BA3F006E87" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. kosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and and 
<taxonomicName id="FD92463A6340EB10C3EC499A8B53BF5D" genus="S." lsidName="S. jinggangshanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="jinggangshanensis">
<emphasis id="AE4CA54A75B6036468136768D4D89717" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. jinggangshanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the closely touching spermathecae (vs slightly separated in 
<taxonomicName id="47BD8B293A465ECDA4DE32589551154B" genus="S." lsidName="S. kosi" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="kosi">
<emphasis id="6BA9630E8001BF069E8C5EE9B7A75942" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. kosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F945F98C6B6A13A36F0A6B920501D699" genus="S." lsidName="S. jinggangshanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="jinggangshanensis">
<emphasis id="04B49D2F50EA002A0735D5817D5B78C6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. jinggangshanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). It also resembles seven other species, 
<taxonomicName id="F6B7C6066DE73A957E3D4FFB1C7D25EB" genus="S." lsidName="S. annae" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="annae">
<emphasis id="2F7BCE948C342F98A6B1715A353345AB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. annae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
